## 3. Cloning a Repo

```bash
mkdir -p ~/Projects && cd ~/Projects
git clone git@github.com:REPO_USERNAME/repo_name.git
cd repo_name

git remote -v   # verify remote is set correctly
```

---

## 4. Branching

```bash
git checkout -b feature/initial-structure   # create + switch to new branch
git switch -c feature/initial-structure     # same thing, modern syntax

git branch              # list local branches
git branch -m new-branch-name	# Rename the current branch
git branch -m old-branch-name new-branch-name 	# Rename different local branch
git branch -d branch-name   # delete a branch
```

**Naming convention** (the `/` is just a folder-like grouper, not a Git feature):

| Prefix | Used for |
|---|---|
| `feature/` | New functionality |
| `fix/` or `bugfix/` | Bug fixes |
| `hotfix/` | Urgent production fixes |
| `chore/` | Maintenance, config, cleanup |
| `docs/` | Documentation only |
| `lab/` | Homelab-specific work |

