## 7. File & Folder Operations

| Action | Shell command | Git command | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Create file | `touch file.txt` | — | No git equivalent |
| Create folder | `mkdir folder` | — | Git ignores empty folders entirely |
| Delete file | `rm file.txt` | `git rm file.txt` | `git rm` stages the deletion too |
| Move/rename | `mv old new` | `git mv old new` | `git mv` preserves rename history |

### Empty folders aren't tracked by Git

```bash
mkdir logs tools playbooks
git status   # nothing shows — Git doesn't track empty dirs

# Fix: add a placeholder file
touch logs/.gitkeep tools/.gitkeep playbooks/.gitkeep
git add .
```

### Useful inspection commands

```bash
git ls-files              # files Git is tracking
git ls-files --others     # untracked files
git ls-files --ignored    # ignored files
git status --ignored      # status including ignored files
git check-ignore -v file  # check if/why a file is ignored
```

